<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
    <h1>Dropdowns</h1>
    <p class="u-mb-5">All dropdowns must be enclosed in <code>section.Dropdown</code>, which contains a button or "trigger," and a dropdown wrapper <code>.Dropdown</code>. Within the wrapper, there is a header (optional) and inner (content). To align the dropdown button to the right of the container like in the examples below, include a utility class of <code>.u-textAlignRight</code> on the parent.</p>

    <p class="u-mb-5">After dropdowns are open, they will remain open unless one of two conditions are met: the user clicks outside the dropdown, or clicks on an action within the dropdown. We can prevent an action from closing the dropdown by adding <code>data-dropdown-leave-open</code> to the action markup.</p>
  </div>
</div>


<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
    <h2>Standard Dropdown</h2>

    <div class="row">
      <div class="small-8 columns">
        <p>This type of dropdown is meant to handle any type of content within it. In this case, we are including a form inside the dropdown.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="small-4 columns u-textAlignRight">
        <section class="Dropdown">
          <a class="Button Icon--arrowDown" data-toggle="dropdown">Transfer Snapshot</a>
          <div class="Dropdown-content">
            <div class="Dropdown-header">
              <h4>Transfer Snapshot</h4>
            </div>
            <div class="Dropdown-inner">
              <p class="small-dark u-mb-3">This will transfer this snapshot to another user. Should the user accept you will lose access.</p>
              <input type="text" class="u-mb-3" placeholder="Here is an input">
              <input type="submit" value="Submit" class="Button Button--fullWidth Button--blue">
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

